{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionLarge language models (LLMs) [11,37,30] are increasingly employed to support software engineers in the generation, testing and repair of code [15,14,27].",
    "Generative AI can, however, not only generate code, but also provide explanations of the inner workings of code and give arguments about its correctness.",
    "This raises the question whether LLMs can also support formal software verification.In this paper, we provide a first step towards answering this question.",
    "In general, one can imagine various ways of supporting verifiers, depending on the verification approach they employ.",
    "Central to all verifiers are, however, techniques for dealing with loops."
  ]
}